.TH "audit_signal_info" 9 "audit_signal_info" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
audit_signal_info \- record signal info for shutting down audit subsystem
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" audit_signal_info
.BI "(int sig "  ","
.BI "struct task_struct *t "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sig" 12
signal value
.IP "t" 12
task being signaled
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the audit subsystem is being terminated, record the task (pid)
and uid that is doing that.
